{In this informational we would like to mention the people who helped in the creation of this course. We would also like to take this opportunity to quickly introduce ourselves. Huy is a 14-year-old FM from Vietnam with a FIDE rating of 2410 at the time of writing, who loves chess very much and has several notable achievements in the tournament circuit. Besides that, he has published one previous course on the Spielmann-Indian, an original repertoire which received lots of positive feedback. On the other hand, MakkaPakka is a mere 1800 chess enthusiast - for now! Funnily enough, both of us happen to play the French Defence ourselves, the very opening this repertoire is designed against! Luckily for us, we can’t take all the credit, and there are some others we should thank here. First of all are the beta testers: Deet, flakefly, BTrix, and Dragonshark. Each of them did an excellent job, and their feedback and suggestions were invaluable. We would also like to thank chessable user kapibarr who was an alpha tester of the course, and provided us with feedback and suggestions since quite early on in the journey of making this course, and the course wouldn’t have been quite the same without their help. Next, there is chessable author and user NM Elijah Logozar, who supported this course with very motivating feedback. In the same vein, we would like to thank the many other chessable users whose interest in the project led to what you see now. The chessable team, of course, also deserves special mention, without them, the course could not have seen the light of day. There were many people working behind the scenes, and in particular, we would like to thank FM Christoph Kuberczyk who did a great job guiding us through the whole process. Lastly, and perhaps most importantly, we want to thank all of you who chose to read these words and study the course, because without you, we had much less reason to work on this project for the past two years. Thank you! Banh Gia Huy and MakkaPakka} 1. Z0 *

