{Black made several moves with his knights in the opening, ignoring the development of other pieces. Punish this crime!} 12. Bb5+ $1 {A crushing tactic. Black cannot block with ...c6 since the e4-knight would be hanging.} Ke7 13. d3 {The knight controls a few important squares so let's drive it back.} (13. Nf3 {is also winning. Not surprisingly with such a king on e7 Black can't survive.}) 13... Nd6 {What's the killer blow? There are as many as four ways for White to mate in two moves in this position. Choose the most disrespectful way to end the game :)} (13... Qd6 14. Be5 Qa3+ 15. Kb1) (13... Nxg5 14. Ba3+ c5 15. d4) 14. Qf6+ gxf6 15. gxf6# {Black's king is trapped by its own pieces. A humiliating finish! However, there is no shame on the Internet.} 1-0

