 the 10...f5 line [/variation/23953369] with} 12. gxf6 Nxf6 13. f3 {with promising compensation for the sacrificed pawn, given Black's poor development and exposed king.}) {Grabbing this pawn is best. Besides winning a pawn, Black is ready to eliminate White's light-squared bishop.} 12. gxh6 gxh6 ({Opening the g-file is beneficial for us since we have a lead in development and our rook will have a great time enjoying the open file. A simple count reveals that while we're temporarily a few pawns down, we have many more pieces developed and ready for action. Black should be fine engine-wise after both} 12... gxh6 {and}) (12... Rxh6 {, but in either case, we can confidently say that the road is full of dirt and potholes for them. It's more than enough for any ordinary player on the streets to know up until this point, however we have gone the extra mile for those who are interested!}) {Looks like a safer, more human choice.} 13. c4 $5 {Setting a poisonous trap.} Nc6 14. Qxe4 Nxf1 15. Nf4 exf4 16. Qxf4 Rf8 17. Bf6 $13 {Black is currently two pieces up, but White has strong compensation due to Black's trapped king in the centre. Provided that Black defends accurately, he can survive the attack, although it's a difficult task.} *

