 force.}) 9... Nc6 ({A natural move, simply developing a piece.} 9... e5 $5 {can be met by} 10. g5 {and if Black insists on keeping the pawn with} Ng4 11. Bh3 f5 {we have} 12. gxf6 {breaking up Black's structure} Nxf6 13. Bxc8 Rxc8 14. Nh3 $1 {followed by Ng5xe4 and c4 with a potential attack.}) 10. g5 {Driving the knight away.} Ne8 11. Qxe4 Nd6 12. Qg2 $16 {The queen does not hinder kingside development from g2 and moreover, Her Majesty supports kingside expansions with h5-g6.} *

