ack has a myriad of move-orders here, but the only thing you need to know is the strategic plan we will show.}) 9... Nc6 (9... b6 {would be ideal, preparing Bb7, if not for the smashing} 10. h4 $1 Bb7 11. Bg2 {when g4-g5 arrives with brute force. 9...Bd7 10.Bg2 e5 11.h3 is similar to what we will be examining now.}) 10. h3 $1 {The next step is to bolster the g4-pawn in order to prepare Bg2-Qe3-Ne2.} e5 (10... Bd7 {can be met with} 11. Bg2 O-O-O 12. Qe3 {, following the grand plan. Next is Ng1-e2-g3-e4, regaining the pawn and keeping the bishop pair.}) 11. Bg2 {Let us remind you once more that we are sticking to the plan!} Bd7 12. Qe3 O-O-O 13. Ne2 Z0 ({Mission completed! Despite being a pawn down, White controls the situation with the power of the bishop pair. Ng3-e4 is available and Nc3-d5 is another idea to increase the pressure. Black is cramped and lacks a target to attack, which makes his position difficult to handle. White is not objectively better against the machine, but Black needs to find many accurate moves -} 13... h5 $1 {a good start - to maintain the balance.}) *

