1. e4 {Welcome aboard! In this chapter, we shall tackle 5... Be7, one of Black's most respected methods to combat the Horwitz Attack. We highly recommend that you check out the Open Horwitz Introduction chapter [/course/82991/21] (if you have not already) before proceeding to study anything in this chapter.} e6 2. b3 d5 3. Bb2 dxe4 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. Qe2 Be7 {You will definitely face this line during your journey with 2. b3 against the French. It is natural and logical to put the bishop on e7, intending ...O-O. Black stays flexible with the queenside pieces, keeping Nbd7/Nc6 and b6-Bb7 options open.} 6. Nxe4 {First subtlety. By avoiding castling, White discourages the ...a5-a4 raid followed by ...c7-c6 as we've seen here. Next, we'll play Nf3 (another useful waiting move) to force Black to show his hand.} O-O 7. Nf3 {Developing the other knight and delaying queenside castle one more move. Before delving into the various alternatives, we want to offer a summary of White's battle strategy:} a5 $5 (7... Nc6 {and}) (7... b6 {are good moves, but they obstruct the ...a5, a4, c6 plan mentioned at the start of the chapter, so White happily castles. 7...a5 and 7...Nbd7 keeps the aforementioned plan [/variation/29257092] available for Black, so White insists on delaying O-O-O.}) {Black launches his counterplay right away. A rule of thumb in the Open Horwitz is that we should meet ...a5 with a4. Let's do it.} 8. a4 c6 ({Stopping Black's queenside expansions. Black has} 8... Nc6 {,}) (8... Nbd7 {and}) (8... b6 {here, but we will not cover these moves separately because the ideas for both sides are identical to 7...Nc6 , 7...Nbd7 and 7...b6 respectively. The inclusion of a-pawn moves does not alter the position much, and in the case of 8...Nc6 we have a direct transposition to this variation [/variation/29257099] . Let's check what happens if Black goes for another path.}) {Our king is not on c1 so there's no need to worry. We even have a rook on a1 to protect the a4-pawn in case of ...b5, so Black's move is a waste of time.} 9. g4 {We recommend that you start the attack on the kingside immediately. The initiative is in White's hands.} *

