1... a5 {Intending ...a4 to open the a-file.} 2. Rh3 {The rook comes to action via an unusual route! You will see the rooklift theme later.} a4 {...a4 as expected, however it is met by} 3. a3 $1 {A common idea! The knight comes to b4 often, followed by this ...a5 attack. However, we can respond with a3 kicking the knight back after which we close the queenside.} Nc6 {The knight must retreat...} 4. b4 {and the queenside is closed, and the whole ...a5 idea neutralised! White has all the time in the world to prepare for the decisive breakthrough on the kingside.} *

