ok which allows us to press in an admittedly still complicated middlegame. After the text, we can choose to play on or take the perpetual.}) 14. Nh5+ (14. Nxh7+ $5 {is an interesting attempt to continue the game. The position is extremely complicated, and we don't want to dive deep into all the nuances of it, so we will only present you the main line of our analysis. It runs} Ke7 15. Nf6 Kf7 16. Nh3 $5 {Otherwise, White can claim a perpetual in a similar fashion to the main line.} Rxh3 $1 {is the only move to avoid being worse. After} 17. gxh3 e5 $1 18. Nd7+ $1 Ke7 19. Nxf8 Nxb3 20. axb3 e4 $1 21. Qxe4+ Kxf8 {the endgame is level. An inhuman sequence which we cannot understand fully. Can you?}) 14... Ke8 15. Nf6+ {The draw is a logical result after a bloodthirsty fight from both sides.} *

