 but it shouldn't work.}) 14... O-O 15. h6 {Creating a potential weakness in Black's position.} g6 16. O-O Qc8 17. c4 $17 {Black is objectively better, but White's practical compensation should not be underestimated either. Conclusion: The Dubov Gambit is a fascinating try that leads to double-edged and fun play. So why not try this out in games with faster time controls? However, even though we've tried hard, we couldn't make this gambit work against the engine and with best play, Black should emerge better. Even though in practice we still have a lot of chances, it would be a dubious decision to make the Dubov Gambit our main recommendation. Let's move on to the principled 4.e5!} *

