re: The French Defence by Cyrus Lakdawala as well as GM Vallejo's video series on Chess24. We're at the critical tabiya of the whole 3...Nf6 complex, and Black has several options to proceed. We will check them one by one.} Be7 {Black prepares castling and strikes in vintage French style with ...f6. Warning for the second player: in the lines which he castles, it wouldn't be strange if the king comes under fire!} 8. Nd2 $5 {Generally, we want to play Nd2 as soon as we develop the bishop to d3. The reason is that we want to have the option of Bb1 available in case Black hits our bishop with cxd4 followed by Nb4. Moreover, we can play Ndf3 in case the d4-pawn is severely attacked and this original concept has scored an 'ordinary' 100% in online games. Impressed? Play the Horwitz!} cxd4 {Black exploits the fact that our knight has committed to the d2-square and clears the tension in the centre as we no longer have the option of Nc3. However, exchanging a more central pawn (c5) for the c3-pawn can hardly be called an impressive achievement.} 9. cxd4 Nb4 $5 {Black uses the fact that the b4 square is accessible and hits the bishop.} 10. Bb1 $1 {The advantage of our 8th move is revealed: a handy retreating square for the bishop is created! Now, it's not clear what that knight is doing on b4.} Nc6 ({The engine suggests dropping back with the knight, a clear sign that something has gone wrong with Black's position.} 10... a5 11. a3 $1 Nc6 12. Ne2 {transposes to the mainline.}) 11. Ne2 a5 (11... f6 $2 12. Nf4 {+- is a terrifying and winning attack, so Black must strive for counterplay on the other side.}) 12. a3 $1 {The recipe to contain Black's counterplay is to block the queenside!} a4 13. b4 Nb6 14. Bd3 $14 {White is a lot better in this position. Black's counterplay probably needs a million light years to succeed, while our space advantage on the kingside granted by the e-pawn that Black allowed to advance with 3...Nf6 guarantees us a continuing initiative. Next, we can simply continue with O-O and slowly expand with g3-h4, Re1 and more depending on the situation.} *

