n and regain the d4-pawn, with an overwhelming development advantage. With only one piece developed, Black has gotten into a serious mess. Let us show you a sample line!} c6 ({Probably the most natural move for a human, but objectively, returning the material with} 11... Be7 {is better. We can play} 12. Nb5 $1 Qd8 13. Nxd4 {with a huge lead in development and an advantage.}) 12. Nc4 Qd8 13. a4 $16 {Black is in huge trouble despite being a pawn up. Just look at their clumsy pieces on the back rank and you'll understand why! Our idea is to push Ary further with a5-a6, activating the rook and creating havoc in Black's camp.} *

